From: ato-zen
Date: 2026-06-13
Subject: Remove 4-space indent from Hermes CLI responses

Remove the default 4-space indentation from streamed responses and the
rich Panel padding in Hermes CLI. This makes responses align flush-left
with the prompt, saving horizontal space.

diff --git a/cli.py b/cli.py
index a9e379141..21de5ff96 100644
--- a/cli.py
+++ b/cli.py
@@ -1654,7 +1654,7 @@ _ACCENT_ANSI_DEFAULT = "\033[1;38;2;255;215;0m"  # True-color #FFD700 bold — fallback
 _BOLD = "\033[1m"
 _RST = "\033[0m"
-_STREAM_PAD = "    "  # 4-space indent for streamed response text (matches Panel padding)
+_STREAM_PAD = ""  # 0-space indent for streamed response text
 
 def _hex_to_ansi(hex_color: str, *, bold: bool = False) -> str:
@@ -10424,7 +10424,7 @@ class HermesCLI(CLIAgentSetupMixin, CLICommandsMixin):
                         border_style=_resp_color,
                         style=_resp_text,
                         box=rich_box.HORIZONTALS,
-                        padding=(1, 4),
+                        padding=(1, 0),
                         width=self._scrollback_box_width(),
                     ))
